President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key positions in his administration. These include Matthias Mitman of Virginia as the Executive Secretary of the National Security Council, Christopher W. Oliver of Alaska as a Member of the International Pacific Halibut Commission, Thomas Luebke of Maryland as a Member of the Committee for the Preservation of the White House, and David Miracle of Ohio as a Member of the Ohio River Valley Water Sanitation Commission. Additionally, there are nominations for members of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council and the Presidio Trust Board of Directors.